A high-performance, lightweight Luau event utility.
It provides stream-like interactions for Luau signals, featuring O(1) connection management, native type safety, and memory-safe iterations.

--// Api Refrence \\--
  --[[StreamEvent(Class)]]--


  StreamEvent.new()
  Constructs a new StreamEvent stream manager instance.
    Returns: StreamEvent object.

  StreamEvent:Connect(fn: (...any) -> ())
  Subscribes a listener function to the stream.Arguments: fn — The callback function to run when fired.
    Returns: A Connection object.

  StreamEvent:Once(fn: (...any) -> hone)
    Subscribes a listener function that automatically disconnects after firing exactly once.Arguments: fn — The callback function.
    Returns: A Connection object.

  StreamEvent:Wait()
    Yields the current thread / scope until the stream is next fired.
    Returns: The arguments passed to the stream when fired.

  StreamEvent:Fire(...: any)
    Fires the stream and schedules all active listeners using task.spawn.
    Arguments: ... — Variadic arguments passed to all listeners.

  StreamEvent:DisconnectAll()
    Mass-disconnects all existing active connections instantly.
    Leaves the stream reusable.

  StreamEvent:Destroy()
    Disconnects all listeners, clears internal tables, and destroys the stream object.
    Full cleanup of the module.


--[[Connection(Object)]]--
  The object returned by :Connect() and :Once().

  Connection.Connected
    Type: boolean
    Description: Returns whether the connection is currently active.

  Connection:Disconnect()
    Deactivates the listener and removes it from the stream's internal tracking registry.
    Connection()
      Metamethod: __callDescription: Syntactic sugar. Calling the connection object as a function directly invokes :Disconnect().




--// Basic Examples \\--

-- Basic Connection & Firing
[[
local StreamEvent = require(path.to.StreamEvent)

-- Create a new stream
local onPlayerLevelUp = StreamEvent.new()

-- Connect a listener
local connection = onPlayerLevelUp:Connect(function(playerName: string, newLevel: number)
    print(string.format("%s leveled up to %d!", playerName, newLevel))
end)

-- Fire the stream
onPlayerLevelUp:Fire("David Zucchini", 50) 
-- Prints: David Zucchini leveled up to 50!
]]

-- Disconnecting and Calling Shortcuts
[[
local connection = untitledStream:Connect(print)

-- Standard disconnection
connection:Disconnect()

-- Shortcut disconnection (calling the connection directly)
connection() 

]]

-- Using Once & Wait
[[
-- Fires only on the very next frame, then drops
myStream:Once(function(data)
    print("This will only log once:", data)
end)

-- Thread yielding
task.spawn(function()
    print("Waiting for data...")

    local result = myStream:Wait()

    print("Resumed with data:", result)
end)
]]

-- Stream Cleanup
[[
-- Clears all current connections, but the stream remains open for new ones
myStream:DisconnectAll()

-- Destroys the stream entirely and breaks the object reference
myStream:Destroy()
]]
(Info: You can also wrap StreamEvent around any other cleanup modules to cleanup multiple streams or tasks within ur game)
